Grammy award-winning singer Burna Boy has opened up a little bit about his relationship, giving an insight on his ‘type’ of woman. In a brief interview with English journalist and Youtuber, Amelia Dimoldenberg on her web series “Chicken Shop Date,” the Afro-fusion superstar revealed the exact qualities he looks out for in a lady. According to ‘Odogwu’, he loves a lady that wouldn’t stress him as well as one who can cook, especially jollof. Speaking further, Burna also made it known that he prefers to keep his relationship private, ‘on the low’.   #BBNaija – Ebuka speaks on Groovy’s alleged bad…     Three popular female celebrities vying for political offices     BBNaija S7: It’s too early to kiss you, Groovy tells Beauty   Dimoldenberg asked; “What would you say your type is in a woman?” Responding, the ‘African Giant’ said: “As long as you don’t stress me, I‘m good. For me, it’s a minus for any lady who doesn’t know how to cook. I need to be cooked for. Meals like jollof ………” When asked if he preferred his relationship to be public or on the low, he replied, “On the low.”